<TITLE> Ports asked to hoist Signal-3 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 5 (bdnews24.com)Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla maritime ports have been asked to hoist local cautionary Signal-3 as a low over the north-western Bay of Bengal led to widespread rain throughout the country Saturday morning, a met official said. The low may head in a north-westerly direction and all fishing boats and trawlers have been advised to stay close to the shore, met official Rasheduzzaman told bdnews24.com. Barisal, Khulna and Rajshahi have been experiencing heavy rain from Saturday morning, local bdnews24.com correspondents report. 
